<p class="MsoPlainText"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class="MsoPlainText">WARNING: It appears that your OpenFabrics subsystem is configured to only allow registering part of your physical memory.&nbsp; This can cause MPI jobs to run with erratic performance, hang, and/or crash.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoPlainText"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class="MsoPlainText"><o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoPlainText"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class="MsoPlainText">This may be caused by your OpenFabrics vendor limiting the amount of physical memory that can be registered.&nbsp; You should investigate the relevant Linux kernel module parameters that control how much physical memory can be registered,
 and increase them to allow registering all physical memory on your machine.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoPlainText"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class="MsoPlainText"><o:p></o:p></p>
